## Key Findings & Visualizations

### 1. Spatial Distribution (Where?)
> **Insight:** Fires are highly concentrated in the **Mediterranean and Aegean coastal zones** (Forest Fires) and **Southeastern Anatolia** (Agricultural Stubble Burning).
![Map](Plots/Map.png)

### 2. Seasonal Analysis (When?)
> **Insight:** There is a strict seasonal cycle. Fire activity rises in June and reaches its **absolute peak in August and September**.
![Monthly](Plots/Monthly.png)

### 3. Annual Trend (Trends & Anomalies)
> **Insight:** While **2009** had the highest frequency of fire counts (mostly agricultural), **2021** stands out as a catastrophic climate-driven anomaly ("Mega-fires").
![Yearly](Plots/Yearly.png)

### 4. Primary Causes (Why?)
> **Insight:** **Negligence (45%)** is the leading cause of forest fires, far exceeding natural causes like lightning. This indicates that most fires are preventable.
![Causes](Plots/Lollipop.png)

### 5. Rehabilitation Efforts (Recovery)
> **Insight:** Recent data (2020-2024) shows a strategic shift in rehabilitation efforts towards the **maintenance** of existing forests rather than new afforestation.
![Rehab](Plots/Afforestation.png)

